A 21-year-old woman presents to her physician with a swelling on her neck. On examination, she is diagnosed with an infection within the carotid sheath. Which of the following structures would be damaged?

options.label: A
options.text: Vagus nerve and middle cervical ganglion

options.label: B
options.text: Internal carotid artery and recurrent laryngeal nerve

options.label: C
options.text: Internal jugular vein and vagus nerve

options.label: D
options.text: Sympathetic trunk and common carotid artery

questions.correct_answer: C. Internal jugular vein and vagus nerve

questions.text: A 65-year-old man with multiple vision problems comes to the local eye clinic. The pupillary light reflex can be eliminated by cutting which of the following nerves?

options.label: A
options.text: Short ciliary, ophthalmic, and oculomotor nerves

options.label: B
options.text: Long ciliary, optic, and short ciliary nerves

options.label: C
options.text: Oculomotor, short ciliary, and optic nerves

options.label: D
options.text: Optic and long ciliary nerves and ciliary ganglion

questions.correct_answer: C. Oculomotor, short ciliary, and optic nerves
